Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Louis L. Stanton: Initial Pretrial Conference held on 1/31/2020. (Court Reporter Eve Giniger) (ml)

SCHEDULING ORDER: The parties propose that fact depositions be concluded by the close of fact discovery, June 19, 2020. Amended Pleadings due by 4/10/2020. Joinder of Parties due by 4/10/2020. Status Conference set for 6/19/2020 at 12:00 PM before Judge Louis L. Stanton. Fact discovery shall be completed by June 19, 2020 and expert discovery shall be completed by September 11, 2020. Plaintiff's anticipate that trial of Plaintiffs' copyright claims can be completed in eight trial days or fewer. The case will be tried to a jury. Defendants anticipate that trial of Plaintiffs' copyright claims can be completed in eight trial days or fewer. To the extent that there remain any issues of fact after the conclusion of the summary adjudication phase of the case, such issues will be tried to a jury. (Signed by Judge Louis L. Stanton on 1/31/2020) (mro) Modified on 2/3/2020 (mro). (Entered: 02/03/2020)
